&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for someone who is a self starter who can demonstrate a thorough working knowledge of commissioning in urgent care and who has a proven track record in delivering effective outcomes in complex situations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will be expected to pick up and manage a key piece of work requiring skills and experience in effective liaison with primary and secondary care colleagues, clear demonstrable abilities in evidence based analysis and the ability to implement complex systems in the current urgent care environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post will be for a period of 6months as a fixed term contract subject to review before the end of that period. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ian Armitage&lt;/p&gt;
